x + \dfrac{x}{360}
x - \dfrac{x}{720}
24
12
\dfrac{x}{360} + \dfrac{x}{720} = 24 \implies \dfrac{x}{240} = 24 \implies x = 5760 \text{ hours} = 240 \text{ days}
\dfrac{x}{360} + \dfrac{x}{720} = 12 \implies \dfrac{x}{240} = 12 \implies x = 2880 \text{ hours} = 120 \text{ days}
 4 \times 60 \times 12
120 \equiv 1 \pmod{7}
